{
  "texts": [
    "All the obtained IMFs components are then fed into the BILSTM model for PV power forecasting.",
    "The developed approach proves its performance compared to other forecasting models (EEMD-BILSTM, EEMD-LSTM, ANN, LSTM, VMD-GRU, EEMD-ANN, and BILSTM) models.",
    "40, proposed multi-stages for short PV power forecasting.",
    "In the first stage, the random forest algorithm RF is used to rank the most important exogenous input and then remove the irrelevant data, then the selected factors are moved as weighted values to the improved grey (IGIVA) to select days with identical weather patterns.",
    "Time series PV power is decomposed using complementary ensemble empirical mode decomposition (CEEMD)."
  ]
}